    • addIfMax

      public static void addIfMax(Organization organization)
      Adds an organization to the collection if it has the maximum value based on the natural ordering. If the collection is empty, the organization is added automatically.
      Parameters:
      organization - The organization to be added.

    • updateElement

      public static void updateElement(Organization newOrganization, Integer ID)
      Updates an element in the collection with the specified ID. The attributes of the organization are updated with the attributes of the newOrganization.
      Parameters:
      newOrganization - The updated organization.
      ID - The ID of the organization to be updated.

    • clearCollection

      public static void clearCollection()
      Clears the collection by removing all organizations. The removed organizations are stored in the clearList.

    • removeElement

      public static void removeElement(Integer ID)
      Removes an organization from the collection based on its ID.
      Parameters:
      ID - The ID of the organization to be removed.

    • filterStartsWithFullName

      public static void filterStartsWithFullName(String fullName)
      Filters and prints organizations in the queue whose full name starts with a given string.
      Parameters:
      fullName - The string to check the full name of organizations.

    • printFirstElement

      public static void printFirstElement()
      Prints the first element in the queue. If the queue is empty, displays the message "Collection is empty!".

    • printElementWithMinimalCreationDate

      public static void printElementWithMinimalCreationDate()
      Prints the element with the minimal creation date in the queue. If the queue is empty, displays the message "Collection is empty!".

    • printUniquePostalAddress

      public static void printUniquePostalAddress()
      Prints unique postal addresses from organizations in the queue. If the queue is empty, displays the message "Collection is empty!".

    • removeLowerElement

      public static void removeLowerElement(Organization organization)
      Removes organizations in the queue that are lower than the given organization. If the queue is empty, displays the message "Collection is empty!".
      Parameters:
      organization - The organization to compare with.

    • rollBack

      public static void rollBack(int steps) throws EmptyCollectionException
      Rolls back the specified number of steps by undoing the previous commands. Throws an EmptyCollectionException if the commandOrders map is empty.
      Parameters:
      steps - The number of steps to roll back.
      Throws:
      EmptyCollectionException - If the commandOrders map is empty.

      fileName - The name of the file to load the collection from.
